<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.0 Strict//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml1/DTD/xhtml1-strict.dtd">
<html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"><head>
<meta charset="utf-8" />
<title>CSS Text 6.1. Hyphenation Control: the hyphens property</title>
<link href="mailto:jeremychen@mozilla.com" rel="author" title="Chun-Min (Jeremy) Chen" />
<link href="https://www.mozilla.org" rel="author" title="Mozilla" />
<link href="https://drafts.csswg.org/css-text-3/#valdef-hyphens-auto" rel="help" />
<link href="reference/hyphenation-control-1-ref.xht" rel="match" />
<meta content="Test checks that automatic hyphenation opportunities within a word
must be ignored if the word contains a conditional hyphen (足 or U+00AD), in favor of the
conditional hyphen(s)." name="assert" />
<style>
code {
  display:block;
  hyphens:auto;
  border: 1px solid black;
}
</style>
</head>
<body lang="en-us">
<!--
  Hyphenation opportunities of the texts in this test are as follows,

        frag[A]ilis[A]tic[C]ex[A]pi[A]ali

  where [A] is an automatic hyphen, and [C] is a conditional hyphen.

  In this test, we set width to somewhere after the conditional hyphen,
  then we see if automatic hyphen breaks are ignored correctly.
-->
<code style="width:12ch;">
fragilistic足expiali
</code>
<br />
<code style="width:14ch;">
fragilistic足expiali
</code>
<br />
<code style="width:16ch;">
fragilistic足expiali
</code>


</body></html>